<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="865" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d865">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/399.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Special
                                    Representative</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your June 22. Falkner assumes that you have promised nothing concerning
                            debts not scheduled, as he does not know whether they can be settled out
                            of the proceeds of the loan, but if it is possible he will urge such
                            settlement. You will so state to the German creditors and you will if
                            possible ascertain the amount of such debts growing out of direct
                            relations of the firms to the Government, but not including Government
                            paper which they have discounted for individuals.</p>
                        <p>There is a claim by the German Post Office against the Liberian
                            Government not included in schedule, the nature and amount of which you
                            will ascertain; Falkner will try to have it settled from the loan
                            proceeds if possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>